==Release==
A competition was run when the game was released. The final screen contained a message to the player. The first person to complete the game and send this message to the ''[[Your Sinclair]]'' competition address would receive 15 games from the ''Your Sinclair'' library.<ref name=yoursinclair25 /> Six [[runners-up]] also received three games each.<ref>{{cite magazine|title =Monty Challenge |date =March 1988 |url =https://archive.org/details/your-sinclair-27/page/n5/mode/2up |magazine =[[Your Sinclair]] |publisher =Dennis Publishing|issn=0269-6983|issue =27 |page =7}}</ref> In a retrospective article from 2003, ''[[GamesTM]]'' called ''Moley Christmas'' an "especially popular" cover game, and further praised it as a "great example" of video game publishers using Christmas to market their games to a wider audience.<ref>{{cite magazine|title =A Very Retro Christmas! |date =December 2003 |url =https://archive.org/details/gamesTM013/page/n141/mode/2up |magazine =[[GamesTM]] |publisher =Highbury Entertainment |issue =13 |pages =150â€“153|issn=1478-5889}}</ref>

